Model.Name: tutorial3
Model.Description:
This tutorial introduces the following concepts:
- Arrays of variable values - Functions that operate on arrays of values - Functions that create constants and arrays of constant values (Constant and Array) - Non-uniform domain grids
The model in this example is identical to the model used in the tutorial 1. Some additional equations that calculate the total flux at the bottom edge are added to illustrate the array functions.
